# Esports Hub - Windsurf Rules

## Project Context
**Name:** Esports Hub
**Type:** blockchain_social_network
**Description:** A platform where athletes and fans can trade digital collectibles, participate in prediction markets, and engage in AR-powered fantasy sports leagues

## Architecture

### Stack
| Layer | Technology |
|-------|------------|
| Frontend | Next.js 14 (App Router) |
| Language | TypeScript (strict) |
| Styling | Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui |
| Database | Supabase (PostgreSQL) |
| Auth | Supabase Auth |





### Core Entities
- **Idea**: id, created_at, updated_at, user_id, title, description
- **Crypto**: id, created_at, updated_at, user_id, name, symbol
- **Stadium**: id, created_at, updated_at, user_id, name, description

### Key Features
- social_feed:must
- auth:must
- user_profile:must
- digital_collectibles:must
- prediction_markets:must
- ar_fantasy_leagues:must
- messaging_system:should
- crypto_wallet:should
- idea_submission:must
- crypto_stadium_token:must

## Coding Standards

### File Naming
- Components: `PascalCase.tsx`
- Utilities: `kebab-case.ts`
- Types: `types.ts` or `[feature].types.ts`
- Hooks: `use-[name].ts`

### TypeScript Rules
```typescript
// ✅ Good
type User = {
  id: string;
  email: string;
  createdAt: Date;
};

// ❌ Bad
interface User {
  id: any;
  email: any;
}
```

### Component Structure
```typescript
// 1. Imports
import { useState } from 'react';
import { cn } from '@/lib/utils';

// 2. Types
type Props = {
  title: string;
  onAction?: () => void;
};

// 3. Component
export function MyComponent({ title, onAction }: Props) {
  // hooks first
  const [state, setState] = useState(false);

  // handlers
  const handleClick = () => {
    setState(true);
    onAction?.();
  };

  // render
  return (
    <div className="p-4">
      <h1>{title}</h1>
      <button onClick={handleClick}>Action</button>
    </div>
  );
}
```

### Supabase Patterns
```typescript
// Server Component
import { createClient } from '@/lib/supabase/server';

export default async function Page() {
  const supabase = await createClient();
  const { data } = await supabase.from('items').select('*');
  return <ItemList items={data} />;
}

// Client Component
'use client';
import { createClient } from '@/lib/supabase/client';

export function ClientComponent() {
  const supabase = createClient();
  // ...
}
```

## Project Structure
```
├── app/
│   ├── (app)/              # Protected routes
│   │   ├── dashboard/
│   │   ├── settings/
│   │   └── layout.tsx      # Auth check
│   ├── (public)/           # Public routes
│   │   ├── page.tsx        # Landing
│   │   └── login/
│   ├── api/                # API routes
│   └── layout.tsx          # Root layout
├── components/
│   ├── ui/                 # shadcn components
│   └── [feature]/          # Feature components
├── lib/
│   ├── supabase/
│   │   ├── client.ts
│   │   ├── server.ts
│   │   └── middleware.ts
│   └── utils.ts
├── hooks/
├── types/
└── supabase/
    └── schema.sql
```

## Quality Checklist
- [ ] TypeScript strict mode, no `any`
- [ ] Zod validation for all inputs
- [ ] RLS policies on all tables
- [ ] Loading and error states
- [ ] Mobile responsive
- [ ] Accessible (ARIA labels, semantic HTML)

## Commands
```bash
npm run dev      # Start dev server
npm run build    # Production build
npm run lint     # Run ESLint
npm run typecheck # TypeScript check
```
